<H2>Situations Available</H2>
<hr>
ATTORNEY. OPENING FOR a member of the bar to litigate in state and federal courts on behalf of employees challenging abuses of compulsory labor unionism. Litigation experience is desirable but not required. Outstanding law-school record is a requirement, and law-review experience is preferred. Strong commitment to the philosophy of individual freedom and free enterprise is necessary for success. The National Right to Work Legal Defense Foundation was established in 1968 to provide legal assistance to employees who suffer injustices concerning the collection and spending of forced union dues, union violence, hiring hall discrimination, and other abuses of coerced unionism. Applications, including a detailed resume, salary requirements, a legal writing sample, three references, and a transcript of law-school grades, should be directed to: Legal Director, National Right to Work Legal Defense Foundation, Suite 600, 8001 Braddock Road, Springfield, Virginia 22160. For further information on the Foundation and issues of law consult our Web site: http://www.nrtw.org.
